channel.title: I wanna hear some Hip-Hop
channel.description: Post your links to your Hip-Hop (or hip-hop “inspired”) tracks below and I’ll listen and give some feedback. I’ll listen and give feedback to each one. This is by far my favorite genre so I’m interested to hear what you have.

item.title: I wanna hear some Hip-Hop
item.dc:creator: therealejoc
item.description:
I’m gonna be completely honest, I didn’t like it that much. It didn’t sound very trap or hip hop to me (except for maybe the 808s). It was missing a lot of drums, which I consider a huge part of hip hop. And the rolling snares sounded more EDM ish than hip hop. Obviously not everything is gonna be perfect but idk if I would listen again. Also, (Not to be too harsh) the song structure would’ve done better (I feel) if there was more of a build up. You kicked it in right away with the 808s and didn’t really build it that much intro wise. I think it has potential, but maybe not as a hip hop/ trap song
